In any case, we'll discuss our meeting today.

> Would it be worth taking the time to reiterate the problem that needs to be resolved, provide a few specific examples that highlight that problem, while being mindful of (and providing examples of) existing $PSModulePath usage scenarios that need to remain supported while solving this problem?

Yeah, I think this would be super helpful. @iSazonov I know we made the definitive statement of what we wanted from the @PowerShell/powershell-committee side in that issue, but I'm not sure even we really know what's going on anymore. 

@rjmholt: @JamesWTruher mentioned that you've taken over some of the module stuff. Might you have some time to look at @iSazonov's build and do a before/after of the behavior?
